# Input Setup Helper
# This file documents the required input actions that need to be configured in Godot's Input Map
# Go to Project Settings -> Input Map and add these actions:

# Movement Actions:
# - move_left: A key, Left Arrow
# - move_right: D key, Right Arrow  
# - move_up: W key, Up Arrow
# - move_down: S key, Down Arrow

# Interaction Actions:
# - interact: E key, Space
# - stealth: Shift, Ctrl

# To set up these actions in Godot:
# 1. Go to Project Settings (Ctrl+Shift+O)
# 2. Select "Input Map" tab
# 3. Add each action name above
# 4. Add the corresponding keys for each action
# 5. Save the project

# The KeyboardPlayerInput class will automatically use these action names
# when checking for input in the update_input() method.